name: Beef Enchiladas II
author: Becky
summary: Simple and quick beef enchiladas. Ground beef and onion are wrapped in flour tortillas, topped with Cheddar cheese and black olives, then baked. This is also great with leftover chicken, shredded beef or turkey. Serve with a green salad or beans and rice.
ingredients: 1 (1.5 ounce) package dry enchilada sauce mix
1 (2.25 ounce) can sliced black olives, drained
directions: Preheat oven to 350 degrees F (175 degrees C)
In a medium skillet over medium high heat, cook the ground beef and onion until beef is evenly browned and onion is tender
Prepare the enchilada sauce according to package directions
Pour 1/4 cup of the sauce into the bottom of a 9x13 inch baking dish
On each flour tortilla, place an equal portion of the ground beef mixture and about 1 ounce of Cheddar cheese, reserving at least 1/2 cup of cheese
Then tightly roll the tortillas and place seam side down in the baking dish
Pour the remaining sauce over the top of the enchiladas and sprinkle with the remaining cheese and olives
Bake in a preheated oven for 20 minutes, or until the sauce is bubbly and cheese is thoroughly melted
